description:
As a QA Engineer testing the Agify.io API
  I want to verify the API functionality and edge cases
  So that I can ensure the API works as expected

elements.name: Successfully predict age for the example name from requirements

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "billybob"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "billybob"
the response should contain a numeric age
the response should contain a count value greater than 0

elements.name: Successfully predict age for a common name

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "michael"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "michael"
the response should contain a numeric age
the response should contain a count value greater than 0

elements.name: Verify response structure and data types

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "alice"
the API should return a successful response
the response should have the correct JSON structure

elements.name: Successfully predict age for various names

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "john"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "john"
the response should contain a numeric age
the response should contain a count value greater than 0

elements.name: Successfully predict age for various names

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "mary"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "mary"
the response should contain a numeric age
the response should contain a count value greater than 0

elements.name: Successfully predict age for various names

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "sarah"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "sarah"
the response should contain a numeric age
the response should contain a count value greater than 0
I request age prediction for name "ROBERT"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "ROBERT"
the response should contain a numeric age
I request age prediction for name "christopher"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "christopher"
the response should contain a numeric age
I request age prediction for name "josé"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "josé"
the response should contain a numeric age
I request age prediction for name "李明"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "李明"
I request age prediction for name "elizabeth"
I request age prediction for name "elizabeth" again
both responses should return the same age
both responses should return the same count
I request age prediction for name "john"
I request age prediction for name "JOHN" again
both responses should return the same age
both responses should return the same count
I request age prediction for name "a"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "a"

the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name ""
the response should have count 0 and null age

the response should contain the name "john123"

the API should return a successful response

the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "mary-jane"
I request age prediction for name "xyzzyx"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "xyzzyx"
the response count might be 0 for uncommon names

elements.name: Successfully predict age for multiple names in batch

steps.name: I send a batch request for multiple names
the API should return a successful response
the batch response should contain all requested names
the batch response should be faster than individual requests
I request age prediction for name "<script>alert('xss')</script>"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "<script>alert('xss')</script>"
the response should not execute any code
I request age prediction for name "'; DROP TABLE users; --"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "'; DROP TABLE users; --"
the response should not execute any code
I send a POST request to the API
the API should return a method not allowed error
the response status should be 404
I request age prediction from wrong endpoint "/api/wrong"
the API should return a not found error
the response status should be 404

elements.name: API response time should be reasonable

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "testuser"
the API should return a successful response
the response time should be less than 5 seconds

elements.name: Successfully predict age with country localization

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "michael" with country "US"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "michael"
the response should contain a numeric age
the response should contain country_id "US"
the response should contain a count value greater than 0

elements.name: Compare age prediction with and without country

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "david"
I request localized age prediction for name "david" with country "US"
both responses should have the same name "david"
the localized response should contain country_id "US"
the global response should not contain country_id
I request age prediction for name "john" with country "INVALID"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "john"
the response should contain country_id "INVALID"
I request age prediction for name "josé" with country "ES"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "josé"
the response should contain country_id "ES"

elements.name: Test Chinese names with China country code

steps.name: I request age prediction for name "王磊" with country "CN"
the API should return a successful response
the response should contain the name "王磊"
the response should contain country_id "CN"
I request age prediction without name parameter
the API should return an error response
the response should contain error message about missing parameter
I request age prediction for extremely invalid name ""
the API should return a successful response
the response should have count 0 and null age
I send many rapid requests to trigger rate limit
the API should either return successful responses or rate limit error
any rate limit error should be handled gracefully
I request age prediction for name "john" with invalid API key "fake-api-key-123"
the API should return an error response
the response status should be 401
the response should contain error message "Invalid API key"
I request age prediction for name "john" with API key "da4f95bdace66006249c72270a5c9cbf"
the API should return an error response
the response status should be 402
the response should contain error message "No active subscription"

name: Agify.io API Age Prediction Testing
